\chapter{Wuhu Local Post}

Wuhu is situated in Anhwei Province on the Yangze River about 282 miles from the sea. It was opened as a Treaty Port in 1876. The Wuhu Local Post was established in 1894 with the first local stamps issued on the 9h of November.

The first stampos depicted wild fowl, a field of rice, a pheasant, a pagoda and the Chinese character for "abundance". The set was lithographed by the Shanghai Lithographic Society. The stamps exist both perforate and imperforate.